reviews.review_text:
Long Second Set Thanx Keith.  I was at this show and have not heard it since.  There are definitely some great moments.  The mix seems a bit cluttered and the vocals hot at times.  
So Many Roads almost always brings the tears, this one no exception.  Promised Land really kicks to uplift the spirits again.
Scarlet>Fire has a nice jam with Jerry playing really fast for this segue.  Nice feel to it.  The Jam out of Terrapin is a great listen.  I like the space, kind of quiet and a bit dark.  Check out Jerry sounding a bit like Carlos during his intro to Watchtower.  I will take Attics anytime!  Worth at least a listen.  Peace
